<br>
You can either solve this problem on your own, or leave it unsolved. What's it going to be ?<br>
<br>
Fuck or be fucked. If you pick 'fuck', here's some ideas for you that are sure to have some fun results.<br>
<br>
 - Grow chardok faction. Invoke fear on any mob about 2 rooms/halls before the raid as they progress.<br>
 - Level 14 clerics with DA bound at the wakening lands sode of kael can make it to the arena raids barely before they die if given SoW and some form of levitate, provided you can diagonal walk decently.<br>
 - Pulling Deep out of lake of ill omen is a nightmare when she's underwater to start with.<br>
 - Broken golem trigger mob dies to almost any offensive spell.<br>
 - Burst of flame on a royal guard followed by hopping into the well will cause the whole room to warp to you down there eventually.<br>
 - Raid targets summon people normally. If you can survive them hitting you for a few seconds to displace them, you'll wind up getting tanks summoned out of cheal range.<br>
 - Most people are too stupid to turn off trading.<br>
 - Frogs in sebilis will stay in the moat without resetting for hours, a little reserve of frogs for you to grab another time. They'll warp out all at once after a while of course.<br>
<br>
Not saying being evil is always the right move, but I'd wager that if that epic-deleting idiot knew his guild had a month of persecution coming to them for his actions, he might have thought twice. Grow just 1 &quot;asshole&quot; and suddenly it start to become not worthwhile to screw with your guild because they just can't force one of their members to play nice (of course on their private board they're encouraging him to train you all again anyways but they won't admit to that). At least then their guild leader would demand him to not delete it since they don't want Galliamius, Akethadar, Saalron, (insert black sheep here) causing more grief over it.<br>
<br>
